            "playUrl": "",
            "metrics": [
                "Gesture detection at 30 FPS with 95 % symbol-recognition accuracy",
                "Delivers translations in 5 target languages with 0.92 BLEU score on average",
                "End-to-end latency under 3 s, designed for 100 requests/min throughput"
            ],
            "longDescription": "Inclusive communication means merging vision and voice - and that's exactly what this in-progress platform does. An OpenCV pipeline captures hand gestures at 30 FPS with 95% recognition accuracy, while a speech-to-text + LLM stack (via LangChain4j) delivers translations into five target languages in under three seconds. Built with modular APIs and accessibility first, it's designed to scale to new symbol sets, dialects, and 100 requests/min throughput for truly global, multi-modal conversations."
